<div class="gl-page">
  <section class="gl-hero"><div class="gl-wrap"><nav class="gl-crumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">&rsaquo;</span><a href="/glossary">Glossary</a><span class="sep">&rsaquo;</span><a href="/glossary/accounting">Accounting</a><span class="sep">&rsaquo;</span><span class="cur">Zoho Custom Modules</span></nav><div class="gl-cat">Accounting Glossary &middot; Core / Software</div><h1 class="gl-h1">What Are Zoho Custom Modules? Definition and How It Works</h1><div class="gl-byline"><span class="ok"><svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg></span><span class="who">Reviewed by CA &amp; CS Team, Patron Accounting LLP</span><span class="sep">&middot;</span><span>Last updated 22 Jul 2026</span><span class="sep">&middot;</span><span>4 min read</span><span class="sep">&middot;</span><span class="lvl">Intermediate</span></div></div></section>
  <div class="gl-tocbar"><div class="gl-wrap gl-toc"><a href="#definition" class="gl-pill is-active">Definition</a><a href="#what-is" class="gl-pill">What it is</a><a href="#how-works" class="gl-pill">How it works</a><a href="#software" class="gl-pill">In software</a><a href="#example" class="gl-pill">Example</a><a href="#mistakes" class="gl-pill">Mistakes</a><a href="#faq-section" class="gl-pill">FAQs</a></div></div>
  <div class="gl-body"><div class="gl-wrap"><div class="gl-grid"><div class="gl-main"><section id="definition" class="gl-sec"><div class="gl-eyebrow">Zoho Custom Modules: Definition</div><div class="definition-box"><p>Zoho Custom Modules are extra record types you add to Zoho Books beyond the standard invoices, bills and expenses, to track information specific to your business. They are created in the Customisation settings and appear as their own module in the app. They matter because they let a business record and report on things the built-in modules do not cover, without leaving its accounting system.</p></div></section><section id="what-is" class="gl-sec"><h2>What Are Zoho Custom Modules?</h2><p>Zoho Books ships with a fixed set of record types — customers, invoices, bills, expenses and so on. A custom module adds a brand-new record type of your own design, with its own fields, so information that has no home in the standard modules can still be captured inside Zoho. It is the difference between forcing data into a notes field and giving it a proper, reportable structure.</p><p>An Indian business reaches for a custom module when its workflow has a record the standard app ignores — a Chennai freight forwarder tracking shipment consignments, a real-estate firm logging property units, or a services company recording contract milestones. The module keeps that operational data alongside the accounts, so it can be filtered, reported and linked to invoices instead of living in a separate spreadsheet.</p><div class="key-terms"><p class="key-terms__title">Key terms</p><ul><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/multi-currency-bank-feed">Multi-Currency Bank Feed</a> — Foreign-currency accounts feeding in with per-line rates.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/xero-bank-rules">Xero Bank Rules</a> — Automatic coding of recurring bank lines in Xero.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/hubdoc-automation">Hubdoc Automation</a> — Document capture that auto-publishes bills into the ledger.</li></ul></div></section><section id="how-works" class="gl-sec"><h2>How Zoho Custom Modules Work</h2><p>A custom module turns a business-specific record into structured, reportable data:</p><ol class="step-cards"><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">1</span><strong>Define the record type</strong><p>You decide what the module represents — say a consignment or a contract — the concept the module will hold.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">2</span><strong>Add the fields</strong><p>Custom fields are created for the data you need to capture, giving each record a consistent structure.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">3</span><strong>Create records</strong><p>Users add records to the module as work happens, building a queryable dataset inside Zoho.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">4</span><strong>Link to standard modules</strong><p>Records can be associated with invoices, customers or bills so the custom data connects to the accounts.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">5</span><strong>Report and filter</strong><p>The module&#x27;s records can be filtered and reported on, replacing an external spreadsheet.</p></li></ol></section><section id="software" class="gl-sec"><h2>How to Set Up Zoho Custom Modules in Zoho Books</h2><p>Custom modules are created from the organisation&#x27;s customisation settings:</p><ol class="step-cards"><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">1</span><strong>Open Settings</strong><p>Click the Gear icon (Settings) in the top-right corner of Zoho Books.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">2</span><strong>Go to Modules</strong><p>Under the Customisation section, select Modules — this lists the standard and any existing custom modules.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">3</span><strong>Create a new module</strong><p>Click + New Module and give it a singular and plural label (for example Consignment / Consignments).</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">4</span><strong>Add custom fields</strong><p>Define the fields the record needs — text, number, date, dropdown — so every record is captured consistently.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">5</span><strong>Set permissions</strong><p>Grant the relevant user roles access to view and edit the module so the right people can use it.</p></li><li class="step-card"><span class="step-num">6</span><strong>Start recording</strong><p>The module now appears in Zoho Books; add records and, where useful, link them to invoices or contacts.</p></li></ol></section><section id="example" class="gl-sec"><h2>Zoho Custom Modules: A Practical Example</h2><div class="gloss-table-wrap"><table class="gloss-table"><thead><tr><th>Particulars</th><th>Amount (INR)</th><th>Treatment</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>Consignment record created (custom module)</td><td>—</td><td>Tracks shipment ref, route, weight</td></tr><tr><td>Linked freight invoice</td><td>85,000</td><td>Standard invoice associated to the consignment</td></tr><tr><td>Fuel surcharge captured in a custom field</td><td>6,000</td><td>Reportable within the module</td></tr><tr><td>Margin report by consignment</td><td>—</td><td>Filtered from the custom module</td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>A Chennai freight forwarder builds a Consignments custom module in Zoho Books with fields for route, weight and fuel surcharge. Each ₹85,000 freight invoice is linked to its consignment record, and a ₹6,000 surcharge is logged in a custom field. Instead of a side spreadsheet, the firm now reports margin per consignment directly from Zoho — operational and financial data in one system.</p></section><div class="gl-callout gl-callout--error"><span class="gl-callout__ic">!</span><div><div class="gl-callout__label">Common error</div><p>Rebuilding a standard module: Creating a custom module for something invoices already do duplicates data → use the built-in module and extend it with custom fields instead.</p></div></div><section id="mistakes" class="gl-sec"><h2>Common Mistakes With Zoho Custom Modules</h2><p>Custom modules add value only when they are designed with restraint:</p><ul class="gloss-bullets"><li><strong>Rebuilding a standard module</strong> — Creating a custom module for something invoices already do duplicates data → use the built-in module and extend it with custom fields instead.</li><li><strong>Too many free-text fields</strong> — Unstructured text fields cannot be reported cleanly → prefer dropdowns and dates so the data stays queryable.</li><li><strong>No link to the accounts</strong> — A module that floats free of invoices and contacts becomes another silo → associate records to standard modules.</li><li><strong>Loose permissions</strong> — Giving everyone edit rights corrupts the data → set role-based access when the module is created.</li></ul></section><section id="related" class="gl-sec"><h2>Related Accounting Terms</h2><p>Related automation and feed concepts:</p><ul class="related-terms"><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/multi-currency-bank-feed">Multi-Currency Bank Feed</a> — Foreign-currency accounts with per-line rates.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/xero-bank-rules">Xero Bank Rules</a> — Recurring bank-line coding in Xero.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/hubdoc-automation">Hubdoc Automation</a> — Auto-publishing captured documents into the ledger.</li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting">Accounting Terms Glossary</a> — Browse every accounting term in one place.</li></ul></section><div class="gl-callout gl-callout--summary"><span class="gl-callout__ic">&#10003;</span><div><div class="gl-callout__label">Quick summary</div><p>Zoho Custom Modules are extra record types you add to Zoho Books beyond the standard invoices, bills and expenses, to track information specific to your business. They are created in the Customisation settings and appear as their own module in the app. They matter because they let a business record and report on things the built-in modules do not cover, without leaving its accounting system.</p></div></div><section class="gl-cta"><div class="gl-cta__t"><h3>Need help with Zoho Custom Modules?</h3><p>Zoho Custom Modules sits inside your day-to-day books. Patron's CA-led team keeps them accurate, compliant and audit-ready.</p></div><div class="gl-cta__btns"><a class="gl-cta__primary" href="/zoho-books-accounting">Zoho Books Accounting &rarr;</a><a class="gl-cta__phone" href="tel:+919459456700">Book a consultation: +91 94594 56700</a></div></section></div><aside class="gl-aside"><div class="gl-card gl-card--service"><div class="gl-card__eyebrow">Related service</div><div class="gl-card__name">Zoho Books Accounting</div><p>CA-led bookkeeping, compliance and reporting for Indian businesses.</p><a class="gl-card__cta" href="/zoho-books-accounting">Explore the service &rarr;</a></div><div class="gl-card"><div class="gl-card__eyebrow">Related services</div><ul><li><a href="/migration-from-tally-to-zoho">Migration: Tally to Zoho Books<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/accounting-services">Accounting &amp; Bookkeeping Services in India<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li></ul></div><div class="gl-card"><div class="gl-card__eyebrow">Related terms</div><ul><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/multi-currency-bank-feed">Multi-Currency Bank Feed<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/xero-bank-rules">Xero Bank Rules<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting/hubdoc-automation">Hubdoc Automation<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li><li><a href="/glossary/accounting">Accounting Terms Glossary<span class="arw">&rarr;</span></a></li></ul></div></aside></div></div></div>
  <section id="faq-section" class="gl-faq-section"><div class="faq-expanded"><aside class="faq-expanded__aside"><h2 class="faq-expanded__title">Zoho Custom Modules FAQs</h2><p class="faq-expanded__lead">Common questions about Zoho Custom Modules for Indian businesses.</p><a class="faq-expanded__cta" href="/contact-us">Still have a question? Talk to a CA &rarr;</a><form class="faq-enquiry" action="https://www.patronaccounting.com/enquiry" method="post" novalidate><h3 class="faq-enquiry__title">Talk to a CA about your books</h3><p class="faq-enquiry__sub">Share your accounting software and we'll scope the work.</p><p class="faq-enquiry__context">Enquiring about: <strong>Zoho Custom Modules</strong></p><input class="faq-enquiry__input" type="text" name="name" placeholder="Your name" required><input class="faq-enquiry__input" type="email" name="email" placeholder="Email" required><div class="faq-enquiry__phone"><span class="faq-enquiry__cc">+91</span><input class="faq-enquiry__input faq-enquiry__input--phone" type="tel" name="phone" placeholder="Mobile" required></div><button class="faq-enquiry__btn" type="submit">Get a Callback</button><p class="faq-enquiry__msg" role="status" aria-live="polite"></p><div class="faq-enquiry__badges"><span class="faq-enquiry__badge"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2.5"><path d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z"/></svg>CA-led team</span></div></form></aside><div class="faq-expanded__list"><div class="faq-expanded__item"><h3 class="faq-expanded__q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-a1">How is a custom module created in Zoho CRM?</h3><div class="faq-expanded__a" id="faq-a1"><p>A custom module is created from Setup, Modules and Fields, Create New Module, where the module is named in singular and plural, fields are dragged in, and a relationship is linked to an existing module such as Accounts. Creation limits depend on the edition. Once live, the module gets its own tab, layout, permissions and API name for integrations.</p></div></div><div class="faq-expanded__item"><h3 class="faq-expanded__q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-a2">What is the difference between a custom module and a custom field in Zoho?</h3><div class="faq-expanded__a" id="faq-a2"><p>A custom field adds one more data point to an existing record, such as a GSTIN box on the Accounts module, while a custom module creates an entirely new record type with its own list view, layout and relationships, such as a Compliance Filings module. Add a field when the data belongs to an existing record, and a module when it has its own life cycle.</p></div></div><div class="faq-expanded__item"><h3 class="faq-expanded__q" aria-expanded="true" aria-controls="faq-a3">Can a Zoho custom module be used for GST and TDS tracking in India?</h3><div class="faq-expanded__a" id="faq-a3"><p>A custom module can store GSTIN, filing status, TDS section and challan details and can trigger reminders, but it does not file anything, since GSTR-1, GSTR-3B and TDS returns go through the GST portal and TRACES. Treat it as a compliance tracker that sits alongside the books, and reconcile it monthly against GSTR-2B and Form 26AS.</p></div></div></div></div></section>
